TY  - JOUR
T1  - Strategic Leadership and Organizational Learning
AU  - Vera, Dusya
AU  - Crossan, Mary
Y1  - 2004/04/01
PY  - 2004
DA  - 2004/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2004.12736080
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2004.12736080
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 222
EP  - 240
VL  - 29
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Adopting the strategic leadership perspective, we develop a theoretical model of the impact of CEO and top manager leadership styles and practices on organizational learning. We take a fine-grained look at the processes and levels of organizational learning to describe how strategic leaders influence each element of the learning system. Researchers have implicitly assumed transformational leadership approaches to organizational learning. We challenge this conventional wisdom by highlighting the value of transactional leadership as well.
AB  - Adopting the strategic leadership perspective, we develop a theoretical model of the impact of CEO and top manager leadership styles and practices on organizational learning. We take a fine-grained look at the processes and levels of organizational learning to describe how strategic leaders influence each element of the learning system. Researchers have implicitly assumed transformational leadership approaches to organizational learning. We challenge this conventional wisdom by highlighting the value of transactional leadership as well.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2004.12736080
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2004.12736080
Y2  - 2026/04/24
