TY  - JOUR
T1  - Coordinating New Product Development in Strategic Alliances
AU  - Gerwin, Donald
Y1  - 2004/04/01
PY  - 2004
DA  - 2004/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2004.12736085
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2004.12736085
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 241
EP  - 257
VL  - 29
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - I develop a theory of coordination for joint new product development projects conducted in strategic alliances. This theory identifies coordination gaps or mismatches between required and actual coordination that lead to performance problems. An evaluation of these gaps leads to specifying conditions under which coordination is easier for a project done in an alliance than for the same project done by one company. I also discuss what alliance managers can do to control the size of a project's gaps.
AB  - I develop a theory of coordination for joint new product development projects conducted in strategic alliances. This theory identifies coordination gaps or mismatches between required and actual coordination that lead to performance problems. An evaluation of these gaps leads to specifying conditions under which coordination is easier for a project done in an alliance than for the same project done by one company. I also discuss what alliance managers can do to control the size of a project's gaps.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2004.12736085
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2004.12736085
